text: Senefeldera is a plant genus of the spurge family (Euphorbiaceae). Their wood can be used as timber, in handicraft and as firewood. Species include: * Senefeldera inclinata Müll.Arg. - chimbe * Senefeldera macrophylla * Senefeldera multiflora * Senefeldera verticillata == References == Category:Hippomaneae Category:Euphorbiaceae genera
title: Senefeldera
